Pomona and Flora there unsold all their charms‚ and walls and sky-compearing crags protect the treasures The Palladium and the Vestal lire were not more watched3 neither the labyrinth nor Hypermnestra's prison was so secure, nor Erichthonius's coffer, nor Danae's brazen tower. LXXX. DE HORTO VULTURNI.

Divitis hic, hospes, Vulturni conspicis hortum, Septaque mortali non superanda pede. Delicias Pomona suas hic explicat omnes, F locaque purpureos pandit amoena sinus. Ardua murorum moles, et proxima caelo Has illibatas saxa tuentur opes. Non ita Palladium custodivere Quirites, Nobile Vestalis nec penetrale foci. Non ita semivirum quae sepsit machina monstrum, Carcer Hypermnestrae non ita tutus erat. Sed nec Erichthonium sic clausit cista Minervae, Nec dominam pluvii turris ahena Iovis. Sunt alii rerum domini, Vulturne, suarum, Tu custos horti mancipiumque tui es.
